# No file extensions in imports

Do not add `.js`, `.ts`, or other extensions to relative import paths. Bun's module resolution handles this automatically.

```typescript
// BAD
import { foo } from "./utils.js";
import { bar } from "./helpers.ts";

// GOOD
import { foo } from "./utils";
import { bar } from "./helpers";
```

Exception: keep `.js` extensions on imports from external packages that require them (e.g. `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk`), since those are part of the package's published export map.
